# 🎓 NUST Admissions Chatbot — Setup Guide

A fully **local, offline** AI chatbot for NUST admission guidance.
No internet needed after setup. No API keys. No cloud.

---

## 📋 Requirements

| Requirement | Minimum                           | Recommended     |
| ----------- | --------------------------------- | --------------- |
| RAM         | 8 GB                              | 16 GB           |
| Storage     | 5 GB free                         | 10 GB           |
| OS          | Windows 10 / Ubuntu 20 / macOS 12 | Any             |
| Python      | 3.10+                             | 3.11            |
| GPU         | Not required                      | NVIDIA (faster) |

---

## 🚀 Step-by-Step Setup

### Step 1 — Install Ollama

Ollama runs AI models locally on your machine.

**Windows / macOS:**
Download from https://ollama.com/download and install.

**Linux:**

```bash
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh
```

### Step 2 — Download AI Models

Open a terminal and run:

```bash
# The main language model (~4.7 GB)
ollama pull llama3.1:8b

# The embedding model (~274 MB)
ollama pull nomic-embed-text
```

Wait for both to download completely.

### Step 3 — Set Up Python Environment

```bash
# Create a virtual environment (recommended)
python -m venv nust_env

# Activate it
# Windows:
nust_env\Scripts\activate
# Linux/macOS:
source nust_env/bin/activate

# Install all dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install Playwright browser (for scraping JS pages)
playwright install chromium
```

### Step 4 — Scrape NUST Data

```bash
python nust_scraper.py
```

This will:

- Visit 50+ NUST admissions pages
- Extract all text content and FAQs
- Save everything to the `nust_data/` folder
- Takes about 5–10 minutes (has polite delays)

### Step 5 — Build the Knowledge Base

```bash
python ingest.py
```

This will:

- Read all scraped files from `nust_data/`
- Split them into chunks
- Create embeddings using Ollama
- Save the vector database to `nust_db/`
- Takes about 2–5 minutes

### Step 6 — Run the Chatbot

```bash
# Make sure Ollama is running (open a separate terminal)
ollama serve

# In your main terminal, run the chatbot
streamlit run chatbot.py
```

Open your browser at: **http://localhost:8501**

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
nust-chatbot/
│
├── nust_scraper.py      ← Scrapes NUST website
├── ingest.py            ← Builds vector database
├── chatbot.py           ← Main chatbot UI
├── requirements.txt     ← Python dependencies
│
├── nust_data/           ← Created by scraper
│   ├── *.txt            ← Scraped page content
│   ├── _all_faqs.txt    ← All FAQs combined
│   └── _scrape_report.json
│
└── nust_db/             ← Created by ingest.py
    ├── chroma.sqlite3   ← Vector index
    └── [uuid folders]/  ← Embedding data
```

---

## 🔄 Updating the Data

When NUST updates their website (new admissions cycle, new fees, etc.):

```bash
# 1. Re-scrape the website
python nust_scraper.py

# 2. Rebuild the database
python ingest.py

# 3. Restart the chatbot
streamlit run chatbot.py
```

---

## ⚙️ Customization

### Change the AI Model

In `chatbot.py`, line 18:

```python
LLM_MODEL = "llama3.1:8b"    # Default
# Options:
# LLM_MODEL = "mistral:7b"    # Slightly faster
# LLM_MODEL = "llama3.1:70b"  # Much better, needs 40GB RAM
# LLM_MODEL = "phi3:mini"     # Very fast, smaller model
```

### Change Answer Style

In `chatbot.py`, edit the `system_prompt` variable to adjust
how the assistant responds.

### Add More Data

Place any additional `.txt` files in `nust_data/` and re-run `ingest.py`.
Great additions: printed brochures, handbooks, admission policies.

---

## 🐛 Troubleshooting

| Problem                         | Fix                                                   |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| `Connection refused` on startup | Run `ollama serve` in a separate terminal             |
| `Database not found` error      | Run `python ingest.py` first                          |
| Scraper gets 403 errors         | Normal — Playwright fallback handles it automatically |
| Slow responses                  | Normal for CPU-only. GPU makes it 5–10x faster        |
| Wrong/outdated answers          | Re-run scraper + ingest to refresh data               |
| `ModuleNotFoundError`           | Run `pip install -r requirements.txt` again           |

